tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul,
  transitioning from a generic look to a calming, sleep-themed design with a new
  color palette, redesigned layouts, and polished UI components. A critical
  console error related to null input values was also identified and fixed.
overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The
  approach involved a comprehensive overhaul of the app's visual design. A new,
  calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced, replacing the previous
  corporate-looking scheme. Key UI components like cards, checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and progress bars were redesigned for a more modern and
  cohesive look. The main questionnaire form and the intro section received
  significant layout and styling updates, including decorative background
  elements and feature cards. All 14 individual questionnaire sections were
  meticulously updated to ensure consistent application of the new theme,
  replacing old gray boxes with refined card-style groupings and improved
  typography. During the process, a console error related to  values being
  passed to input fields was identified and fixed by modifying the
  component to gracefully handle such cases. The outcome is a visually
  appealing, professional, and consistent sleep questionnaire app that aligns
  with its health-focused purpose.
